OL,7,FThe average one-way trip to school for
OL,8,Fpupils with Send is nine miles,
OL,9,Faccording to the research carried out
OL,10,Fby the Isos Partnership, but one
OL,11,Fcounty council reported an average
OL,12,Fdistance of 22.8 miles.
OL,14,FCouncils reported that a "growing
OL,15,Fminority" of children and young people
OL,16,Fwith Send are travelling very long
OL,17,Fdistances to school ` often due to a
OL,18,Flack of suitable special school places
OL,19,Fcloser to their home.
